description.narrative: Through strategic communication, effective documentation, advocacy and volunteerism, UNICEF continued promoting child rights and participation. UNICEF intensified its digital engagement, including content on COVID-19 prevention and response, seeing an increase in social media followers. UNICEF also launched its new website in both English and Kinyarwanda, as well as the Internet of Good Things platform with data-free digital information on COVID-19. Support from private sector partnership projects led to UNICEF reaching out to some of the most vulnerable and marginalized children, especially in the tea plantations and remote districts. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/08/2020
